PUB_PUB_FORMATTED: Westwood, J.O. 1842. Description of a genus of lamellicorn beetles allied to Pachypus. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London 1842: 66

QUALIFICATION: Metascelis flexilis sp. nov. was also published in Westwood, J.O. 1842. Description of a genus of lamellicorn beetles allied to Pachypus. Annals and Magazine of Natural History 11: 68 (68); the holotype appears to be lost and the description is insufficient to allow identification; the type locality is unknown and the species may not be from Australia; Allsopp considers the species is erroneously attributed to Systellopini by Sharp, D. 1877. Descriptions of some new forms of aberrant Melolonthini from Australia: forming a distinct subtribe (Systellopides). Annali del Museo Civico Storia Naturale di Genova 9: 311-320 (311); both the genus and species should perhaps be removed from the Australian list
